verses.text_plain: Bless the Lord, O my soul. O Lord my God, thou art very great; thou art clothed with honour and majesty.
verses.verse_html: 1Bless the Lord, O my soul. O Lord my God, thou art very great; thou art clothed with honour and majesty.

verses.text_plain: Who coverest thyself with light as with a garment: who stretchest out the heavens like a curtain:
verses.verse_html: 2Who coverest thyself with light as with a garment: who stretchest out the heavens like a curtain:

verses.text_plain: Who layeth the beams of his chambers in the waters: who maketh the clouds his chariot: who walketh upon the wings of the wind:
verses.verse_html: 3Who layeth the beams of his chambers in the waters: who maketh the clouds his chariot: who walketh upon the wings of the wind:

verses.text_plain: Who maketh his angels spirits; his ministers a flaming fire:
verses.verse_html: 4Who maketh his angels spirits; his ministers a flaming fire:

verses.text_plain: Who laid the foundations of the earth, that it should not be removed for ever.
verses.verse_html:
5Who laid the foundations of the earth, that it should not be removed for ever. ▼
▼ Who…: Heb. He hath founded the earth upon her bases

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Who…: Heb. He hath founded the earth upon her bases
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Who…: Heb. He hath founded the earth upon her bases

verses.text_plain: Thou coveredst it with the deep as with a garment: the waters stood above the mountains.
verses.verse_html: 6Thou coveredst it with the deep as with a garment: the waters stood above the mountains.

verses.text_plain: At thy rebuke they fled; at the voice of thy thunder they hasted away.
verses.verse_html: 7At thy rebuke they fled; at the voice of thy thunder they hasted away.

verses.text_plain: They go up by the mountains; they go down by the valleys unto the place which thou hast founded for them.
verses.verse_html:
8They go up by the mountains; they go down by the valleys unto the place which thou hast founded for them. ▼
▼ They go up…: or, The mountains ascend, the valleys descend

footnotes.body_text: ▼ They go up…: or, The mountains ascend, the valleys descend
footnotes.body_html: ▼ They go up…: or, The mountains ascend, the valleys descend

verses.text_plain: Thou hast set a bound that they may not pass over; that they turn not again to cover the earth.
verses.verse_html: 9Thou hast set a bound that they may not pass over; that they turn not again to cover the earth.

tokens.text: that they may not pass over

verses.text_plain: He sendeth the springs into the valleys, which run among the hills.
verses.verse_html:
10He sendeth the springs into the valleys, which run among the hills. ▼
▼ He: Heb. Who
 , ▼
▼ run: Heb. walk

verses.text_plain: They give drink to every beast of the field: the wild asses quench their thirst.
verses.verse_html:
11They give drink to every beast of the field: the wild asses quench their thirst. ▼
▼ quench: Heb. break

verses.text_plain: By them shall the fowls of the heaven have their habitation, which sing among the branches.
verses.verse_html:
12By them shall the fowls of the heaven have their habitation, which sing among the branches. ▼
▼ sing: Heb. give a voice

footnotes.body_html: ▼ sing: Heb. give a voice

verses.text_plain: He watereth the hills from his chambers: the earth is satisfied with the fruit of thy works.
verses.verse_html: 13He watereth the hills from his chambers: the earth is satisfied with the fruit of thy works.

verses.text_plain: He causeth the grass to grow for the cattle, and herb for the service of man: that he may bring forth food out of the earth;
verses.verse_html: 14He causeth the grass to grow for the cattle, and herb for the service of man: that he may bring forth food out of the earth;

verses.text_plain: And wine that maketh glad the heart of man, and oil to make his face to shine, and bread which strengtheneth man’s heart.
verses.verse_html:
15And wine that maketh glad the heart of man, and oil to make his face to shine, and bread which strengtheneth man’s heart. ▼
▼ oil…: Heb. to make his face shine with oil, or, more than oil

footnotes.body_text: ▼ oil…: Heb. to make his face shine with oil, or, more than oil
footnotes.body_html: ▼ oil…: Heb. to make his face shine with oil, or, more than oil

verses.text_plain: The trees of the Lord are full of sap; the cedars of Lebanon, which he hath planted;
verses.verse_html: 16The trees of the Lord are full of sap; the cedars of Lebanon, which he hath planted;

verses.text_plain: Where the birds make their nests: as for the stork, the fir trees are her house.
verses.verse_html: 17Where the birds make their nests: as for the stork, the fir trees are her house.

verses.text_plain: The high hills are a refuge for the wild goats; and the rocks for the conies.
verses.verse_html: 18The high hills are a refuge for the wild goats; and the rocks for the conies.

verses.text_plain: He appointed the moon for seasons: the sun knoweth his going down.
verses.verse_html: 19He appointed the moon for seasons: the sun knoweth his going down.

verses.text_plain: Thou makest darkness, and it is night: wherein all the beasts of the forest do creep forth.
verses.verse_html:
20Thou makest darkness, and it is night: wherein all the beasts of the forest do creep forth. ▼
▼ beasts…: Heb. beasts thereof do trample on the forest

footnotes.body_text: ▼ beasts…: Heb. beasts thereof do trample on the forest
footnotes.body_html: ▼ beasts…: Heb. beasts thereof do trample on the forest

verses.text_plain: The young lions roar after their prey, and seek their meat from God.
verses.verse_html: 21The young lions roar after their prey, and seek their meat from God.

verses.text_plain: The sun ariseth, they gather themselves together, and lay them down in their dens.
verses.verse_html: 22The sun ariseth, they gather themselves together, and lay them down in their dens.

verses.text_plain: Man goeth forth unto his work and to his labour until the evening.
verses.verse_html: 23Man goeth forth unto his work and to his labour until the evening.

verses.text_plain: O Lord, how manifold are thy works! in wisdom hast thou made them all: the earth is full of thy riches.
verses.verse_html: 24O Lord, how manifold are thy works! in wisdom hast thou made them all: the earth is full of thy riches.

verses.text_plain: So is this great and wide sea, wherein are things creeping innumerable, both small and great beasts.
verses.verse_html: 25So is this great and wide sea, wherein are things creeping innumerable, both small and great beasts.

verses.text_plain: There go the ships: there is that leviathan, whom thou hast made to play therein.
verses.verse_html:
26There go the ships: there is that leviathan, whom thou hast made to play therein. ▼
▼ made: Heb. formed

verses.text_plain: These wait all upon thee; that thou mayest give them their meat in due season.
verses.verse_html: 27These wait all upon thee; that thou mayest give them their meat in due season.

tokens.text: all upon thee; that thou mayest give

verses.text_plain: That thou givest them they gather: thou openest thine hand, they are filled with good.
verses.verse_html: 28That thou givest them they gather: thou openest thine hand, they are filled with good.

verses.text_plain: Thou hidest thy face, they are troubled: thou takest away their breath, they die, and return to their dust.
verses.verse_html: 29Thou hidest thy face, they are troubled: thou takest away their breath, they die, and return to their dust.

verses.text_plain: Thou sendest forth thy spirit, they are created: and thou renewest the face of the earth.
verses.verse_html: 30Thou sendest forth thy spirit, they are created: and thou renewest the face of the earth.

verses.text_plain: The glory of the Lord shall endure for ever: the Lord shall rejoice in his works.
verses.verse_html:
31The glory of the Lord shall endure for ever: the Lord shall rejoice in his works. ▼
▼ endure: Heb. be

verses.text_plain: He looketh on the earth, and it trembleth: he toucheth the hills, and they smoke.
verses.verse_html: 32He looketh on the earth, and it trembleth: he toucheth the hills, and they smoke.

verses.text_plain: I will sing unto the Lord as long as I live: I will sing praise to my God while I have my being.
verses.verse_html: 33I will sing unto the Lord as long as I live: I will sing praise to my God while I have my being.

verses.text_plain: My meditation of him shall be sweet: I will be glad in the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 34My meditation of him shall be sweet: I will be glad in the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Let the sinners be consumed out of the earth, and let the wicked be no more. Bless thou the Lord, O my soul. Praise ye the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 35Let the sinners be consumed out of the earth, and let the wicked be no more. Bless thou the Lord, O my soul. Praise ye the Lord.
